  "explanation": "## Iptg/Tetracycline Toggle Switch\n**Pattern:** Toggle Switch\n**Organism:** Escherichia coli\n\n### Description\nBistable toggle switch: IPTG drives state A (GFP), tetracycline drives state B (RFP)\n\n### Transcription Units\n- **promoter_a**: PLlac/ara Promoter -> RBS B0034 -> TetR Repressor -> RBS B0034 -> GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) -> Double Terminator B0015 (1666 bp)\n- **promoter_b**: PLtet Promoter -> RBS B0034 -> LacI Repressor -> RBS B0034 -> mRFP1 (Red Fluorescent Protein) -> Double Terminator B0015 (1977 bp)\n\n### Regulatory Connections\n- promoter_a --[activates]--> repressor_a\n- promoter_a --[activates]--> reporter_a\n- repressor_a --[represses]--> promoter_b\n- promoter_b --[activates]--> repressor_b\n- promoter_b --[activates]--> reporter_b\n- repressor_b --[represses]--> promoter_a\n\n### Component Details\n- **promoter_a** (promoter): PLlac/ara Promoter -- IPTG-inducible promoter from the lac operon. Repressed by LacI, induced by IPTG.\n- **repressor_a** (repressor): TetR Repressor -- Tet repressor. Binds tet operator and represses PLtet. Released by tetracycline/aTc.\n- **reporter_a** (reporter): GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) -- Green fluorescent protein. Emits at 509 nm.\n- **promoter_b** (promoter): PLtet Promoter -- Tetracycline-inducible promoter. Repressed by TetR; tetracycline or aTc releases TetR.\n- **repressor_b** (repressor): LacI Repressor -- Lac repressor protein. Binds lac operator and represses transcription. IPTG releases LacI.\n- **reporter_b** (reporter): mRFP1 (Red Fluorescent Protein) -- Monomeric red fluorescent protein. Emits at 607 nm.\n\n**Total construct:** ~3643 bp across 2 transcription unit(s)",
